      </app>
      <app loc="6">
        <lem>-m<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>ṇik<choice><orig><unclear cert="low">k</unclear></orig><reg>y</reg></choice>a-</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:RamachandraMurthy1986_02">-māṇik<choice><sic>k</sic><corr>y</corr></choice>a-</rdg>
        <note>I accept RM's <foreign>-māṇikka-</foreign> on the strength of the exact parallel in line 8 of the <ref target="DHARMA_INSVengiCalukya00018.xml">Zulakallu plates of Vijayāditya I</ref>, but in the published estampage the <foreign>ka</foreign> seems not to be doubled, and <foreign>ma</foreign> does not seem to have an <foreign>ā</foreign> attached to it.</note>
