        <note>Here too, I reconstruct the text on the basis of the <ref target="DHARMA_INSVengiCalukya00018.xml">Zulakallu plates</ref>. In the published estampages, nothing is discernible at the end of line 6 (where RM reads <foreign>ka</foreign>), nor at the beginning of line 7 (where he reads nothing before the descender of <foreign>rjja</foreign> above). However, I find <foreign>-kiraṇa-kara-</foreign> implausible, while there may easily have been a now indistinct <foreign>sa</foreign> at the beginning of line 7.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="11">
        <lem>-vidhūta-</lem>
        <note>The character <foreign>ta</foreign> is quite narrow and may be a correction over something narrower.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="11">
        <lem>-pāpmana<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> niravadyodāra-</lem>
        <note>The characters <foreign>na ni</foreign> are quite narrow and may be a correction over a single character.</note>
