      <app loc="13">
        <lem><unclear>kṣī</unclear>rā<pb n="2v" break="no"/><lb n="14" break="no"/><unclear>r</unclear>ṇṇava Ivātig<choice><sic>ā</sic><corr>a</corr></choice>mbhīra-</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:RamachandraMurthy1986_02">kṣīrā<pb n="2v" break="no"/><lb n="14" break="no"/>rṇṇavair atig<choice><sic>ā</sic><corr>a</corr></choice>mbhīra-</rdg>
        <note>The reading is clear, so this must be some kind of weird typo in RM.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="15">
        <lem>-nika<add place="below">ra</add>-</lem>
        <note>RM's note about the <foreign>ra</foreign> being added below the line is wrongly anchored next to the preceding word, <foreign>timira</foreign>.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="23">
        <lem>viṣṇuś<surplus>ś</surplus>armmaṇaḥ</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:RamachandraMurthy1986_02">viṣṇuśarmmaṇaḥ</rdg>
      </app>
      <app loc="24">
        <lem>-vākyā<choice><sic>t</sic><corr>rth</corr></choice>a-<sic>pramana</sic>-</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:RamachandraMurthy1986_02">-vākya<surplus>ta</surplus>-pram<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice><choice><sic>n</sic><corr>ṇ</corr></choice>a-</rdg>
        <note>I find RM's emendation unsatisfactory. I am confident that <foreign>vākyāta</foreign> is a scribal mistake for <foreign>vākyārtha</foreign> or <foreign>vākyārttha</foreign>, and the vowel of <foreign>kyā</foreign> is quite clear. I am less sure about <foreign>pramana</foreign>, but believe that it may be erroneous for <foreign>pravacana</foreign>, with one character omitted and either <foreign>va</foreign> or <foreign>ca</foreign> mistakenly changed to <foreign>ma</foreign>. It could also be derived similarly, if less easily, from <foreign>pracakṣaṇa</foreign>. Other solutions may well be possible, so I prefer not to show any emendation in the text. Furthermore, the superfluous <foreign>śa</foreign> above the characters <foreign>prabha</foreign> after this word may be relevant. I show read this as <foreign>śśa</foreign> in the previous line, while R apparently ignores it. This could perhaps be a correction intended for this locus, though see also the apparatus to line 25.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="25">
        <lem>Āyu<choice><orig>-m</orig><corr>r</corr></choice>-ārogy<unclear>ā</unclear></lem>
