        <note>The name was read as Raṇḍubaḷḷi for the ARIE report, while RM asserts that it is correctly Reṇḍubaḷḷi. See also the commentary. In my opinion the two dots on either side of the <foreign>ra</foreign>-like glyph leave no doubt that it is a long initial <foreign>Ī</foreign>. As far as I can see from the printed estampage, the second character could be <foreign>ndu</foreign> as well as <foreign>ṇḍu</foreign>, while the third is quite indistinct.</note>
